t-text-stroke-width:=\"\" background-color:=\"\" rgb(255,=\"\" 255,=\"\" 255);=\"\" text-decoration:=\"\" none;\"=\"\"><div class=\"parMainL\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center; caret-color: rgb(33, 37, 41); color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 16px;=\"\" font-style:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-caps:=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" letter-spacing:=\"\" orphans:=\"\" auto;=\"\" text-indent:=\"\" 0px;=\"\" text-transform:=\"\" none;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" widows:=\"\" word-spacing:=\"\" -webkit-text-size-adjust:=\"\" -webkit-text-stroke-width:=\"\" background-color:=\"\" rgb(255,=\"\" 255,=\"\" 255);=\"\" text-decoration:=\"\" none;\"=\"\"><p class=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem;\"><b>You need to have:</b><br>1. Measuring Tape <br>2. Digital Scale </p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem;\"><img src=\"/content/Weight-Tape.jpg?1540654431\" class=\"img-thumbnail\" alt=\"tape measurer\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid rgb(222, 226, 230); padding: 0.25rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 0.25rem; max-width: 100%;\" width=\"304\" height=\"206\">&nbsp; <img src=\"/content/scale.png?1540654431\" class=\"img-thumbnail\" alt=\"Scale\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid rgb(222, 226, 230); padding: 0.25rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 0.25rem; max-width: 100%;\" width=\"197\" height=\"197\"></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem;\"><br></p></div>',3,NULL,NULL),
	(5,'<h2 class=\"av1\">Weight<span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n                      <div class=\"text-center\">\r\n          <img id=\"scale-1\" src=\"/content/scale.png?1540700834\" class=\"picScale2\" alt=\"Scale\"></div><div class=\"text-center\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <br>\r\n        \r\n          <h5 class=\"\">Instructions</h5><p class=\"\">1. Remove your child’s shoes and heavy clothes (i.e. jacket)</p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">2. Have your child standing with both feet in the center of the digital scale</p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">3. Record the weight on the scale</p>\r\n          \r\n           \r\n           <p align=\"center\"> Please enter your Childs <b>weight</b> in Kilograms</p>',5,NULL,NULL),
	(6,'<p>                  </p><h2 class=\"av1\">Height  <span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n        <div class=\"text-center\">\r\n      \r\n          <img src=\"/content/child height.jpg?1540655422\" class=\"picTest\" alt=\"childs height\"></div><div class=\"text-center\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <br>\r\n        \r\n          <h5 class=\"\">Instructions<br></h5><p class=\"\">1. Remove your child’s shoes and heavy clothes (i.e. jacket)</p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">2. Have your child standing with flat feet (together) touching the wall </p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">3. Ask your child to look straight ahead </p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">4. Use something flat (i.e. ruler) to mark the wall </p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">5. Measure the distance from the floor to the mark on the wall. <b>Do not round up.</b></p>\r\n          <hr>\r\n          \r\n           \r\n           <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Please enter your Child height (in centimeters)</p>',4,NULL,NULL),
	(7,'<h2 class=\"av1\">Waist circumference<span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n                     <p class=\"text-center av1\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">As you have measured your child height, now it is time to measure “child’s name” waist circumference.</span></span></p>\r\n        <div class=\"text-center \">\r\n          <img id=\"scale-1\" src=\"/content/waist.jpg?1540704151\" class=\"picScale2\" alt=\"Scale\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <br>\r\n        \r\n          <h5 class=\"\">Instructions</h5><p class=\"\">1. Measure your child waist circumference at a horizontal line one inch above your belly button.<b> Do not round up.</b></p>\r\n          \r\n           \r\n           <br>\r\n           <p align=\"center\"> Please enter your Child <b>Waist circumference</b> in centimeters</p>',6,NULL,NULL),
	(8,'<h2 class=\"text-center text-success\">Fruits and Vegetables</h2>\r\n        <hr>\r\n\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"container text-center\">\r\n          <div class=\"lead\">\r\n          <p class=\"\">To help your child grow and develop, eating fruits and veggies everyday is important part of their health. Is your child eating enough Fruits &amp; Veggies?</p>\r\n          <p class=\"\">Lets find out!.</p>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        \r\n          <div class=\"text-center\">\r\n              <img id=\"vegePic\" class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"/content/Dietary-Introduction.jpg?1540704720\" alt=\"Generic placeholder image\">\r\n          </div>\r\n        \r\n          <hr>',7,NULL,NULL),
	(9,'<h2 class=\"text-center text-success\" align=\"center\">Fruits and Vegetables</h2>\r\n\r\n		<hr align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n		\r\n		\r\n			\r\n				\r\n					<h3 class=\"featurette-heading text-success\" align=\"center\">Fruits <span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h3>\r\n					\r\n						<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">How many serves of fruits does your child usually eat each day?</p>\r\n						<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">A serve is equal to 1 cup of diced pieces. The fruit can be fresh, dried, frozen or tinned fruit.</p>\r\n		              <div align=\"center\">\r\n			              <img id=\"serve-fruits\" class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"/content/serve-fruits.png?1541080243\" alt=\"Generic placeholder image\">\r\n		              </div><p align=\"center\"><br>Serves of Fruits: <span id=\"fruitAmount\" class=\"text-success\"></span></p>\r\n			             \r\n					<div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col align-self-center\">\r\n				\r\n			</div>\r\n                </div>',8,NULL,NULL),
	(10,'<h2 class=\"text-center text-success\">Fruits and Vegetables</h2>\r\n           \r\n      <hr>\r\n\r\n      \r\n\r\n      \r\n        \r\n          \r\n            <h3 class=\"featurette-heading text-success\" align=\"center\">Vegetables <span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h3>\r\n            \r\n              <p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">How many serve of veggies does your child usually eat each day?</p>\r\n              <p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">A serve is equal to 1/2 cup cooked veggies, or 1 cup of salad veggies. The veggies can be fresh, dried, frozen or tinned.</p>\r\n              <div align=\"center\">\r\n                <img id=\"serve-veggies\" class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"/content/serve-veggies.png\" alt=\"Generic placeholder image\">\r\n              </div>',9,NULL,NULL),
	(11,'<h2 class=\"text-center text-danger\">Exercise</h2>	\r\n		<hr>\r\n		<div class=\"container text-center\">\r\n			<div class=\"row\">\r\n				<div class=\"col align-self-center\">\r\n					<p class=\"lead\">For children to grow up healthy, it\'s important that they are exercising every day.</p><p class=\"lead\">Some benefit of exercising includes, feeling less stressed,maintaining a healthier weight, stronger bones and muscle, and becoming more flexible.<br></p>\r\n					<p class=\"lead\">Is your child moving enough? Let\'s find out. <br></p>\r\n					<img id=\"physicalPic\" class=\"img-fluid \" src=\"/content/Exercise-Introduction.jpg?1540707024\" alt=\"Generic placeholder image\">	\r\n				</div>	\r\n			</div>\r\n			<hr>\r\n			\r\n		</div>',10,NULL,NULL),
	(12,'<h2 class=\"text-center text-danger\" align=\"center\">Exercise</h2>						\r\n			<hr align=\"center\">\r\n						\r\n				\r\n					\r\n						\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">Over the past <b>7 DAYS</b>, how many minutes of exercise did your child engaged in on a daily basis?</p>\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">This can be accumulated over the entire day, for example\r\n								in bouts of 10 minutes</p>\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">Moderate to vigorous activity is any activity that\r\n								increases the heart rate and gets you out of breath some of the time.\r\n								Moderate physical activity includes bike riding, skateboarding and dancing.</p>\r\n							\r\n							\r\n							\r\n								<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">Hours and minutes spent exercising daily:</p><span class=\"combodate\"></span>',11,NULL,NULL),
	(13,'<div>\r\n				<h2 class=\"text-center text-info\" align=\"center\">Screen Time</h2>\r\n				</div>\r\n				\r\n			<hr align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n			\r\n				<div class=\"row\">\r\n					<div class=\"col align-self-center\" align=\"center\">\r\n						<p class=\"lead\">Screen time is the time spent looking at the screen. Children are exposed to more screens than ever!</p>\r\n						<img id=\"sedentaryPic\" class=\"img-fluid pb-3\" src=\"/content/Screen-Introduction.jpg?1540708134\" alt=\"Generic placeholder image\" width=\"800px\">\r\n						<p class=\"lead\">It is a problem because too much screen time increases child\'s risk of</p>\r\n						<ul class=\"list-unstyled lead\"><li>Becoming overweight</li><li>Achieving less at school </li><li>Being less able to self-regulate emotions</li></ul></div>	\r\n				</div>',12,NULL,NULL),
	(14,'<div>\r\n				<h2 class=\"text-center text-info\">Screen Time</h2>\r\n				</div>					\r\n			<hr>\r\n\r\n			\r\n			<div class=\"container text-center\">\r\n				<div class=\"row\">\r\n					<div class=\"col align-self-center\">\r\n						<h3 class=\"featurette-heading text-info\">Activity List<span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h3>\r\n						<p class=\"lead\">The following activities involve interacting with screens: <br></p>\r\n						<div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\r\n							\r\n							\r\n						<div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\r\n							\r\n							<ul class=\"list-group border border-info\"><li class=\"list-group-item lead\">Watching TV</li><li class=\"list-group-item lead\">Watching Videos/DVDs</li><li class=\"list-group-item lead\">Using the Computer for fun</li><li class=\"list-group-item lead\">Playing on smart phone or tablet</li><li class=\"list-group-item lead\">Playing computer or video games</li><li class=\"list-group-item lead\"> Using the computer for doing homework</li></ul>\r\n						</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n						\r\n\r\n					</div>	\r\n				</div>\r\n				\r\n				<hr>\r\n				\r\n			</div>',13,NULL,NULL),
	(15,'<div>\r\n				<h2 class=\"text-center text-info\">Screen Time</h2>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<hr>\r\n							\r\n			\r\n				\r\n					\r\n						<h3 class=\"featurette-heading text-info\" align=\"center\">School <span style=\"background-color: inherit;\">Days<span class=\"text-muted\"></span></span></h3>\r\n						\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">Overall, your child has about 8 hours of free time before and after school, some of which is spent on sedentary activities such as screen time.</p>\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">Think about a normal <b>school week</b> How many hours does your child spend looking at the screen before and after school each day?</p>',14,NULL,NULL),
	(16,'<div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\r\n							<div id=\"list\" class=\"border border-success collapse show\" style=\"\">\r\n								<li class=\"list-group-item\">Watching TV</li>\r\n								<li class=\"list-group-item\">Watching Videos/DVDs</li>\r\n								<li class=\"list-group-item\">Using the Computer for fun</li>\r\n								<li class=\"list-group-item\">Playing on smart phone or tablet</li>\r\n								<li class=\"list-group-item\">Playing computer or video games</li>\r\n								<li class=\"list-group-item\">Using the computer for doing homework</li>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>',15,NULL,NULL),
	(17,'<h2 class=\"text-center text-info\">Screen Time</h2>	\r\n			<hr>\r\n			\r\n				\r\n			\r\n				\r\n					\r\n						<h3 class=\"featurette-heading text-info\" align=\"center\"><b>Non</b>-School Days<span class=\"text-muted\"></span></h3>\r\n						\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">“Overall, your child has about 16 hours of free time on a <b>non</b>-school day, some of which is spent on sedentary activities such as screen time.”</p>\r\n							<p class=\"lead\" align=\"center\">Think about a normal <b>non-school day!</b> How many hours does your child spend looking at the screen on a <b>non</b>-school day?</p>',16,NULL,NULL),
	(18,'<div>\r\n				<h2 class=\"text-center text-secondary\"><span style=\"color: rgb(99, 99, 99);\"> Sleeping Habit </span></h2>\r\n				</div>\r\n					\r\n			<hr>\r\n			<div class=\"container text-center\">\r\n				<div class=\"row\">\r\n					<div class=\"col align-self-center\">\r\n						<p class=\"lead\">Lack of sleep affects children’s health and also the ability to learn and do well in school.</p>\r\n						<p class=\"lead\">Is your child getting enough sleep? Let us find out! <br></p>\r\n						<img id=\"sleepPic\" class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"/content/Sleep-Introduction.jpg\" alt=\"Generic placeholder image\">	\r\n					</div>	\r\n				</div>\r\n				<hr>\r\n			</div>',17,NULL,NULL),
